Madras Samayal features traditional and modern recipes which were handed to me by my mother, mother in law and my grand-mother. This cuisine is very peculiar in the aspect that it stimulates the taste buds of all six tastes in every dish prepared and thus satisfying the palette thoroughly. Come on and learn the recipe of these tasty dishes. " Navin Suvai Arumbukkal Malarattum"

Nannilam Brahmasri V Rajagopala Ganapatigal is Salakshana Ganapati and a renowned scholar.  Hailing from a traditional Vedic Deekshitar family,  Ganapadigal is renowned and revered as an authority in the field of Vedic text, scriptures, practical application of Vedic rituals and precise observance of Dharma Sastra. He has won many laurels from distinguished institutions in many fields like Meemamsa, Nyaya, Astrology, Shrowtham, Veda Bhashyam and even Computer Science, to name a few. With profound knowledge in Samskritam a strong footage in Dharamasastra, his contribution in the field of inculcating the essential guidelines from our Sanathana dharma is extraordinary.
